    • Constructor Detail

      • App

        public App(java.lang.String name,
   java.lang.String config,
   java.util.ArrayList<Cmd> commands,
   Tlm[] telemetry,
   int TlmAppID,
   int CmdAppID)
        This is a Command and Telemetry app configured with app-specific parameters, and can represent any Command and Telemetry app. Every app is an instance of this class with app-specific parameters. The parameters are configured from an XML document through the utilities.XMLParser class. This is done through File > Populate Apps and selecting appropriately-formatted XML files on your computer.
        Parameters:
        name - The name to display for this App in the GUI.
        config - The name of the Config, to be displayed in the GUI.
        commands - The commands for this App.
        telemetry - The telemetry for this App.
        TlmAppID - The telemetry msgid. If an incoming packet has a msgid matching this, the packet will be treated as a houskeeping packet to update this App's telemetry values in the GUI.
        CmdAppID - The command msgid. If the CFS has an App whose command msgid matches this, the CFS will treat this as a command packet for the App.

      • setSC

        public final void setSC(java.lang.String SC)
        Sets the "SC" or "Sequence Count" value in this App's telemetry window. This is used when a telemetry packet is parsed for its SC value, and needs to be displayed in the GUI.
        Parameters:
        SC - The string to represent as this App's current Sequence Count.

      • setTime

        public final void setTime(java.lang.String time)
        Sets the Time value in this App's telemetry window. This is used when a telemetry packet is parsed for its Time value, and needs to be displayed in the GUI.
        Parameters:
        time - The string to represent as this App's current Time, as determined by the CFS App.
